# ⚡ Quick Start Guide

Get the Node.js Blog Server API up and running in **5 minutes**!

## 📋 Prerequisites Checklist

Before starting, make sure you have:

- ✅ **Node.js** installed (v14+) - [Download](https://nodejs.org/)
- ✅ **MongoDB** running locally OR [MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas) account
- ✅ **Git** installed - [Download](https://git-scm.com/)

---

## 🚀 5-Minute Setup

### 1. Clone & Install (1 minute)

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/elsayedfarg/Node-JS-Blog-Server.git
cd Node-JS-Blog-Server

# Install dependencies
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment (2 minutes)

```bash
# Copy the example config
cp config.env.example config.env
```

**Edit `config.env` with your text editor:**

```env
# REQUIRED: Database (choose one option)
# Option A - Local MongoDB:
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/blog-api

# Option B - MongoDB Atlas (free):
# MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/blog-api

# REQUIRED: JWT Secret (use any random string for development)
JWT_SECRET=my-super-secret-development-key-123

# OPTIONAL: Email (skip for now, set up later)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# OPTIONAL: ImageKit (skip for now, set up later)
IMAGEKIT_PUBLIC_KEY=your-public-key
IMAGEKIT_PRIVATE_KEY=your-private-key
IMAGEKIT_URL_ENDPOINT=https://ik.imagekit.io/your-id
```

**Minimum Required Config for Testing:**
```env
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/blog-api
JWT_SECRET=my-dev-secret-key
```

### 3. Start the Server (30 seconds)

```bash
# Development mode (with auto-restart)
npm run dev
```

**You should see:**
```
✅ Database connected successfully
🚀 Server running on port 5000 in development mode
```

### 4. Test the API (1 minute)

**Option A - Using Browser:**
Visit: `http://localhost:5000`

**Option B - Using curl:**
```bash
curl http://localhost:5000/api/v1
```

**Option C - Using Postman (Recommended):**
1. Open Postman
2. Import `postman/BlogAPI.postman_collection.json`
3. Import `postman/BlogAPI.postman_environment.json`
4. Select "BlogAPI Environment"
5. Try the "Register User" request

---

## 🎯 First API Calls

### 1. Register a User

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "confirmPassword": "password123"
  }'
```

**Save the token from the response!**

### 2. Create a Post

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/posts \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE" \
  -d '{
    "title": "My First Post",
    "content": "This is my first blog post!",
    "status": "published"
  }'
```

### 3. Get All Posts

```bash
curl http://localhost:5000/api/v1/posts
```

